An inter-ministerial committee is briefing the media on details of government interventions following President Ramaphosa's announcement of the 21-day lockdown in South Africa amid the spread of COVID-19. JOHANNESBURG - Social Development Minister Lindiwe Zulu says Sassa is ready to pay grant payments with pension payments to be made on 30 March and 31 March - all other grants will be paid on 1 April. The minister was speaking at a briefing on Tuesday following President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement of a 21-day nationwide lockdown to curb the spread of the coronavirus. WATCH: Inter-ministerial briefing  Social distancing will be enforced at retailers where payments are made, the minister said. No new applications for grants will be made during the lockdown period, Minister Zulu said. More to follow. To follow EWN's live blog on the briefing click here.